# FFmpeg Integration

## Overview
Guidelines for working with FFmpeg integration in Telecine, including the custom C++ Node.js addon and video processing workflows.

## C++ FFmpeg Addon (`lib/transcode/`)

### Architecture
- **Custom Node.js addon** built with cmake-js
- **FFmpeg 6.1** integration for video processing
- **Async workers** for non-blocking operations
- **libcurl** integration for remote source fetching

### Key Components
```cpp
// Core pipeline components
src/pipeline/          // Video processing pipeline
src/async/            // Async worker implementations
src/logging.cpp       // Logging utilities
src/FFmpegUtils.cpp   // FFmpeg helper functions
```

### Build System
```bash
# Build the C++ addon
npm run build  # Runs cmake-js build --directory lib/transcode

# CMake configuration
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.15)
find_package(PkgConfig REQUIRED)
pkg_check_modules(FFMPEG REQUIRED libavcodec libavformat libavutil libswscale libavfilter)
```

## Video Processing Capabilities

### Supported Operations
- **Format validation** and metadata extraction
- **Keyframe detection** for seeking optimization
- **Byte-range fetching** for remote sources
- **Real-time transcoding** with just-in-time processing
- **Seekable format conversion** for random access

### Format Requirements
- **Seekable formats only** - requirement for random access points
- **Efficient seeking** to arbitrary timestamps
- **Lower bitrate transcoding** on demand
- **ISOBMFF support** (ISO Base Media File Format)

